AI Usage Reflection

1. Which AI tool or LLM model did you use, and why did you choose it?
I used ChatGPT (GPT-5.3). I chose this tool mainly to help clean up and structure my answers.


2. How did you use it during the assignment?
I used it as a support tool to identify mistakes and improve the structure and clarity of my answers. 
It was not used to generate the core analysis.


3. Approximately how much time did you spend using it?
Approximately 1–2 hours in total, mainly during the writing and revewing phase of the assignment.


4. Which part of your solution benefited the most from it?
It was most useful for reviewing my answers and improving their clarity, consistency, and overall structure.


5. What was the biggest drawback or limitation?
The AI sometimes suggested changes to my conclusions that did not align with my experimental observations. 
This highlighted that AI outputs cannot always be trusted in engineering analysis, especially from a QA perspective.


6. How did you validate the AI-generated output before submitting your final answer?
I validated all suggestions by comparing them with my own analysis and the actual experimental/log data. 
I rejected thoes suggestions that were not supported by evidence.


7. Were there any suggestions from the AI tool that you decided not to use? Why?
Yes, I chose not to use suggestions that modified my conclusions when they conflicted with my experimental findings. 
Maintaining accuracy based on real data was prioritized.


8. What part of the final submission best reflects your own independent reasoning?
All technical reasoning, analysis, and conclusions reflect my own independent work. 
The AI was only used to improve presentation and polishing.
